An amateur football player collapsed and died on the field on Thursday. Anele Gasa (26) who plays for TP United, a Verulam based football team in Durban, died on Thursday afternoon during a football match. Pram Balram, Reaction Unit South Africa (Rusa) spokesperson, said the match was being played at a football field in Trenance Park. “Gasa collapsed on a soccer field during a match in Trenance Park... He was loaded into the back seat of a blue Renault Clio and rushed to the Rusa base for medical assistance,” he said. “Paramedics found no signs of life and he was declared deceased. His family was informed shortly afterwards.” Gasa lived in the Zwelisha Township in Verulam.